snippet.textDisplay: It is shirk in Islam to worship or ask any person for favors other than God Almighty Allah. Prophet Muhammad PBUH although the most beloved by Allah was still a man. Having said that, this kind of shirk is common in Pakistan and the rest of the world. Some people ask Muhammad PBUH for favors, others Ali or some Pir or pious guy or Jesus etc and the list goes on. God Almighty guide us all to the right path. Amin. Love to all my fellow you tubers who use YouTube for the good of humanity and any other tool for that matter. I guess we can still listen to this and supplant Tajdar e Haram as Allah Almighty rather than our beloved prophet Muhammad PBUH. Beautifully done by Atif. I hope we all become one Muslims and not be divided or belong to different sects and try our best to get the best understanding of Islam so we can succeed in this life and the Hereafter. May Allah guide me if I am wrong and all my fellow believers and even non believers. Allah knows the best. Love to all.
